r s &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-BKC-SCHOOP-LADN     02-03 0309
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-BKC-SCHOOP-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
USC'S BIBBY FIGURES THREE BETTER THAN TWO
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By SCOTT WOLF  
 c.1999 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ After alternating seniors Elias Ayuso and Adam
Spanich at the shooting-guard position, USC coach Henry Bibby has
decided he's most comfortable with both in the lineup. The Trojans
have gone with a three-guard lineup the past two games, as Bibby
tries to find ways to improve his offense.
</P>
<P>
   ``I've probably made enough lineup changes,'' Bibby said. ``I
like Adam and (Elias) starting. I like the one-two punch. When
those guys are playing well, it gives us a chance to win.''
</P>
<P>
   The moves seems to be working. The pair hit 17 of 31 shots from
3-point range the past two games.
</P>
<P>
   __ Going nowhere: Although his playing time has been curtailed
to only 11 minutes per contest in Pac-10 play, junior forward
Jarvis Turner said he has no plans to transfer.
</P>
<P>
   __ Toughest loss: USC's season might have suffered its biggest
setback in late December when sophomore point guard Kevin Augustine
quit the team and decided to transfer. It's meant the Trojans are
down to freshman Brandon Granville and converted shooting guard
Quincy Wilder at the point.
</P>
<P>
   ``What hurts us is Brandon is playing like a freshman and we've
been struggling because we have no other point guards,'' Bibby
said.
</P>
<P>
   What did the loss of Augustine mean? ``It killed us,'' Bibby
said.
</P>
<P>
   __ Faded memory: It's been nearly a month since USC won a
basketball game, on Spanich's miracle half-court shot that enabled
the Trojans to upset Oregon 85-84 on Jan. 7.
</P>
<P>
   Spanich was asked what he would have said if someone told him
that would be USC's last victory for the month of January.
</P>
<P>
   ``I would have thought they were crazy,'' Spanich said. ``I
can't remember what it feels like to win.''
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-02-03-99 0034EST &QL; 
</TRAILER>
