<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-DAILY-NEWS-MEDIA-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
DAILY NEWS FILLS NEW GM POST
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
c.1999 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ The Daily News of Los Angeles announced Tuesday
that veteran Southern California newspaper advertising executive
Bob Gray has been appointed to the newly created post of general
manager, effective March 1.
</P>
<P>
   The appointment was made by Ike Massey, publisher of the Daily
News and president and chief executive officer of the Los Angeles
Newspaper Group, who said, ``Bob Gray has great experience in
sales, marketing and circulation in addition to a keen grasp of
newspaper operations.''
</P>
<P>
   Gray, 48, will handle day-to-day business functions of the Daily
News, including advertising, marketing, circulation, production and
finance. The news and editorial departments of the Daily News will
continue to report to Massey.
</P>
<P>
   Since January 1998, Gray has been advertising director and
assistant to the publisher of the Long Beach Press-Telegram, which
is a member of the Los Angeles Newspaper Group. Gray previously
held a number of advertising management positions for many years at
the Riverside Press-Enterprise and at Cox Publications in Phoenix.
Earlier in his career, Gray held circulation supervisory positions
with the Riverside newspaper.
</P>
<P>
   ``I look forward to working with the employees of the Daily News
and continuing the tradition that has exemplified them as one of
the leading newspapers in the industry,'' Gray said.
</P>
<P>
   In addition to the Daily News and the Press-Telegram, the Los
Angeles Newspaper Group is composed of the San Gabriel Valley
Tribune, the Whittier Daily News and the Pasadena Star-News. Last
month it was announced that the Donrey Media newspapers in Southern
California, including the Inland Valley Daily Bulletin in Ontario,
will merge with the Los Angeles Newspaper Group.
</P>
<P>
   Massey said Gray's appointment will allow him to continue to
oversee the Daily News as publisher as well as to work on the
growing Los Angeles Newspaper Group operations.
</P>
<P>
   ``I'm pleased to be able to have someone the caliber of Bob Gray
available for promotion within our group,'' Massey said. ``This
will give me more time and freedom to work more with our
ever-expanding cluster of newspapers in Southern California.''
</P>
<P>
   Gray and his family moved from Michigan to California 40 years
ago, when he was 8. He and his wife, Faith, have three children.
</P>
<P>
   X X X &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
