did poet Gwendolyn Brooks stop using rhyme after 1967? These
questions are answered during the six-hour PBS series ``I'll Make
Me a World: A Century of African-American Arts'' that captures the
stories behind African Americans' artistic legacy in the 20th
century. (Martin, Austin American-Statesman) MOVED.
