<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-VIDEO-MINIS04-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Mini reviews of movies on video
 &HT;    By Steve Murray and Eleanor Ringel
 &HT;    c. 1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   &QR;  ``Mulan'' (G) _ The best Disney animated feature since
``Beauty and the Beast'' and ``The Lion King.'' Based on a
fourth-century legend, it's about a young girl who pulls a National
Velvet, i.e., disguises herself as a boy and goes to battle in her
elderly father's place. This isn't just a grand family film; it's a
grand film, period. As Eddie Murphy's little red dragon says,
````Mulan, you the man!'' Grade: A
</P>
<P>
   _ Eleanor Ringel
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  ``Shooting Fish'' (PG) _ A comedy that harks back to those
it's-a-gas British '60s flicks . . . only, without the gas. Dan
Futterman (``The Birdcage'') and Stuart Townsend play con artists
who flit through '90s London fleecing rich guys, aided by their
lovely assistant, Georgie (Kate Beckinsale). They make a charming
trio, but they're left dangling by a script that's only moderately
amusing. Grade: C+
</P>
<P>
   _ Steve Murray
</P>
<P>
   Steve Murray and Eleanor Ringel write for the Atlanta
Journal-Constitution.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
