<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Spotlight on Cameron Diaz (`There's something about Mary')
 &HT;    Staff Reports
 &HT;    c. 1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   &QR;  ``The Mask'' _ Already proving that she was more than just a
face, playing the love object in this Jim Carrey FX comedy.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  ``The Last Supper'' _ As a roommate in a house of college
students, who decide to take their sociopolitical philosophy to
murderous extremes.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  ``Head Above Water'' _ A newlywed trying to cover up an
accidental murder in this black comedy co-starring Harvey Keitel
and Craig Sheffer.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  ``My Best Friend's Wedding'' _ Readying to marry Dermot
Mulroney, unaware that his old pal Julia Roberts still has feelings
for him.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  ``A Life Less Ordinary'' _ Singing ``Somewhere Beyond the
Sea'' with Ewan McGregor in this whacked-out comic misfire from the
``Trainspotting'' guys.
</P>
