<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-02-03 12:24 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A9973 &Cx1f; ttj-z
r l &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-GADGETS-HNS &LR;      02-03 0437
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-GADGETS-HNS </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
SPACE SOUNDS GIVE BACH A NEW TWIST 
</HEADLINE>
   (EDs: Phone numbers, Web sites CQ)  
 (For use by New York Times News Service clients.)  
 By STEVE BARNES  
 c.1999 Albany Times Union  
<TEXT>
<P>
   The creators of the new ``Winds of Mars'' recording say the
music, which overlays Bach piano pieces with sounds collected by a
spacecraft, is the ``world's first all-digital, extraterrestrial
music production.''
</P>
<P>
   Not that there's much competition for the honor, but we were
intrigued anyway. During the Pathfinder landing on Mars in 1997 the
craft's weather station recorded the weather on the Red Planet's
surface. A Minneapolis computer expert took the data, ran it
through a synthesizer to create recognizable sounds and manipulated
those sounds to resemble the aural equivalent of the Martian
landscape.
</P>
<P>
   Pianist Roderick Kettlewell plays the 17 Bach solo piano
compositions. The recording, at about $15 for cassette and $20 for
CD, shipping included, may be ordered online at
http://www.windsofmars.com or by calling (612) 338-5461.
</P>
<P>
   &UR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   POOCH PRIMPING: Origins, that body-products-and-makeup company,
has moved into the non-human market with a trio of items set for
release this spring. First up is Comb Improvements Dog Detangler, a
``miracle mixture'' that ``magically untangles, conditions and
moisturizes dogs' coats with a natural pleasant fragrance.''
</P>
<P>
   The spray blends oils, including lavender, geranium, oakmoss and
patchouli, together with wheat protein to condition, detangle and
make grooming more pleasurable. There's also a dog shampoo and
Guard Dog Spray, which sounds like doggy deodorant. It combines
citronella, tansy flower, eucalyptus and oat extract to reduce the
dog's stink and soothe its skin.
</P>
<P>
   The products, to be rolled out now through May, will be
available wherever Origins products are sold or by calling
800-ORIGINS (674-4467).
</P>
<P>
   &UR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   HOME PHONES: Herewith, according to a recent survey commissioned
by Sony, is a look at who we are, at least as defined by how we use
our home telephones:
</P>
<P>
   _ The average American household has three telephones, one of
which is cordless.
</P>
<P>
   _ Average at-home daily phone use by women is a little more than
40 minutes; by men, a little less than 25 minutes.
</P>
<P>
   _ A full quarter of American homes have caller ID.
</P>
<P>
   _ Eight out of 10 adults say they receive at least three
unwanted phone calls per day at home.
</P>
<P>
   _ Favorite features, in order of preference, are: caller-ID
display, built-in answering machine and speed dialing.
</P>
<P>
   _ Only 6 percent of homes subscribe to voice mail features
offered by telephone companies.
</P>
</TEXT>
