<HEADER>
A0189 &Cx1f; tad-z
u d &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-FOOD-RECIPESWAP04-COX     02-03 0939
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-FOOD-RECIPESWAP04-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Eggplant `crepes' a rare delicacy
 &HT;    By Marica Langhenry
 &HT;    c. 1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   Because no one sent in a recipe, we flipped through some
cookbooks looking for eggplant pancakes with tomato-basil sauce, as
requested by R.J. Wholehan of Roswell (Ga.). Luckily, we found the
similar-sounding Eggplant ``Crepes'' Sorrento: slices of eggplant
wrapped around cheese filling and smothered with a tomato-basil
sauce. We hope it's the right idea.
</P>
<P>
   MAIN DISH
</P>
<P>
   Eggplant ``Crepes'' Sorrento
</P>
<P>
   Makes 8 servings Preparation time: 1 hour Standing time:
overnight plus 30 minutes Cooking time: about 1 hour, 25 minutes
</P>
<P>
   4 medium eggplants, cut lengthwise into 1/4-inch-thick ovals
(about 6 to 7 slices per eggplant) Salt
</P>
<P>
   3 to 4 tablespoons olive oil
</P>
<P>
   Mushroom-Cheese Filling:
</P>
<P>
   1 tablespoon olive oil
</P>
<P>
   1 large onion, minced
</P>
<P>
   12 ounces fresh mushrooms, sliced
</P>
<P>
   1/4 cup (about) dried mushrooms (preferably cepes), soaked in
1/2 cup warm water for 30 minutes (do not drain)
</P>
<P>
   Salt and freshly ground pepper
</P>
<P>
   12 or more ounces ricotta cheese
</P>
<P>
   1/2 cup each freshly grated Parmesan and Romano cheeses,
preferably imported (about 2 1/2 ounces each)
</P>
<P>
   3 green onions, chopped
</P>
<P>
   1 egg
</P>
<P>
   1 tablespoon chopped fresh basil leaves or 3/4 teaspoon dried,
crumbled basil leaves
</P>
<P>
   1/2 teaspoon chopped fresh oregano or 1/8 teaspoon dried,
crumbled oregano
</P>
<P>
   1/2 teaspoon fresh mint leaves or 1/8 teaspoon dried, crumbled
mint leaves
</P>
<P>
   Tomato-Basil Sauce:
</P>
<P>
   2 tablespoons olive oil
</P>
<P>
   1 large onion, minced
</P>
<P>
   1 large garlic clove, minced
</P>
<P>
   1 1/2 teaspoons chopped fresh basil leaves or generous 1/2
teaspoon dried, crumbled basil leaves
</P>
<P>
   Generous pinch of dried oregano, crumbled
</P>
<P>
   3 cups (29-ounce can) tomato puree
</P>
<P>
   1 tablespoon tomato paste
</P>
<P>
   Salt and freshly ground pepper
</P>
<P>
   6 ounces mozzarella cheese, shredded
</P>
<P>
   Place eggplant in a colander and sprinkle lightly with salt. Set
aside 30 minutes to drain. Rinse under running water; pat dry.
</P>
<P>
   Preheat oven to 475 degrees. Brush large baking sheet with olive
oil. Lightly brush one side of eggplant slices with oil. Arrange
about one-fourth of the eggplant slices, oiled side down, on the
prepared baking sheet. Bake in batches until softened, about 5
minutes. (This can also be done on a baking sheet lined with oiled
aluminum foil; while one batch is baking, the next can be arranged
on another piece of foil.) If time allows, spread baked slices on
paper towels. Top with more paper towels, then weight with a heavy
chopping board. Let stand overnight to drain thoroughly and flatten
slightly.
</P>
<P>
   For the Mushroom-Cheese Filling: Heat olive oil in a large,
heavy, non-aluminum skillet over very low heat. Add onion, cover
and cook slowly to mellow flavor, about 30 minutes, stirring
occasionally. Increase heat to high, add fresh mushrooms and saute
until lightly browned. Add dried mushrooms with liquid and cook
until moisture has evaporated. Let cool. Season to taste with salt
and pepper.
</P>
<P>
   In a large bowl, combine ricotta, Parmesan and Romano cheeses,
green onions, egg, basil, oregano and mint and beat well. Blend in
the cooled mushroom mixture. (Filling can be prepared one day ahead
and refrigerated.)
</P>
<P>
   For the Tomato-Basil Sauce: Heat olive oil in a large, heavy,
non-aluminum skillet over very low heat. Add onion, cover and cook
slowly to mellow flavor, about 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Uncover, increase heat to medium, add garlic, basil and oregano and
stir 30 seconds. Blend in tomato puree and tomato paste with salt
and pepper to taste. Bring to a boil. Let boil until thickened
slightly, about 5 minutes. (Sauce can be prepared up to two months
ahead and frozen.)
</P>
<P>
   Grease a shallow 9-by-13-inch baking dish. Spread about 1
tablespoon filling over each piece of eggplant, leaving a 1-inch
border at the wider end. Starting at the narrower end, roll
eggplant up, jellyroll style. Transfer to prepared baking dish.
(Can be prepared up to one day ahead to this point. Cover tightly
with plastic wrap and refrigerate.)
</P>
<P>
   Preheat oven to 375 degrees. Spread sauce over rolls. Sprinkle
with shredded cheese. Bake until sauce is bubbling and cheese
begins to color, about 30-45 minutes. Serve immediately. _ From
``More of the Best of Bon Appetit'' (Knapp, 1984)
</P>
<P>
   Per serving: 321 calories, 18 grams protein, 19 grams fat
(percent calories from fat, 54), 22 grams carbohydrates, 73
milligrams cholesterol, 347 milligrams sodium, 5 grams fiber.
</P>
<P>
   Requests
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Julie Driggers of Lawrenceville (Ga.) has two requests: ``I am
looking for a coconut layer cake that has coconut milk and sour
cream in the dough. It makes a real moist cake.
</P>
<P>
   ``Also there is a recipe for white icing I use to have ... that
tasted like whipped cream.'' It had whipped cream in it, along with
other ingredients, she said. ``I used to use it with a four-layer
blueberry cake I made with canned blueberries. I hope you can help
me.''
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Elizabeth Ann Wright of Savannah (Ga.) asks for the recipe for
a sweet potato bread pudding with walnuts, old-fashioned bread and
cinnamon covered raisins. She'd also like information about
cookbooks featuring bread puddings.
</P>
<P>
   Where to write
</P>
<P>
   Recipes or requests for recipes for this column should be sent
to Recipe Swap, Food Department, The Atlanta Journal-Constitution,
P.O. Box 4689, Atlanta, GA 30302. Include a daytime telephone
number. E-mail: mlanghenry(at)ajc.com
</P>
<P>
   Marcia Langhenry writes for the Atlanta Journal-Constitution.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
