<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    A gallery of great tomatoes
 &HT;    By Bob Longino
 &HT;    c. 1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   We conducted our own taste comparison of quality canned tomatoes
recommended by Italian cooking experts.
</P>
<P>
   POMI
</P>
<P>
   Net weight: 26 1/2 ounces.
</P>
<P>
   Ingredients: Chopped plum tomatoes.
</P>
<P>
   Color, texture: Crimson; meaty; a bit watery.
</P>
<P>
   Taste: Tangy, but also a tinge of sweetness.
</P>
<P>
   Price: $1.79 at DeKalb Farmers Market (Decatur,Ga.).
</P>
<P>
   Cost per ounce: 6.75 cents.
</P>
<P>
   CENTO
</P>
<P>
   Net weight: 35 ounces.
</P>
<P>
   Ingredients: Whole plum tomatoes, natural juices, basil.
</P>
<P>
   Color, texture: Deep red; slightly watery juice; thick, muscular
pulp.
</P>
<P>
   Taste: Slightly tart, acidic.
</P>
<P>
   Price: $1.79 at Publix.
</P>
<P>
   Cost per ounce: 5.11 cents.
</P>
<P>
   MUIR GLEN
</P>
<P>
   Net weight: 28 ounces.
</P>
<P>
   Ingredients: Organically grown and processed tomatoes and tomato
juice, sea salt, naturally derived citric acid and calcium
chloride.
</P>
<P>
   Color, texture: Slightly orange and yellowy tops; watery juice;
stringy meat.
</P>
<P>
   Taste: Distinctively robust American; salty.
</P>
<P>
   Price: $1.49 at DeKalb Farmers Market.
</P>
<P>
   Cost per ounce: 5.32 cents.
</P>
<P>
   RUSSO
</P>
<P>
   Net weight: 28 ounces.
</P>
<P>
   Ingredients: Whole tomatoes and natural juices.
</P>
<P>
   Color, texture: Deep red; melts in your mouth.
</P>
<P>
   Taste: Slightly sweet.
</P>
<P>
   Price: 99 cents at DeKalb Farmers Market.
</P>
<P>
   Cost per ounce: 3.53 cents
</P>
<P>
   BEL ARIA SAN MARZANO
</P>
<P>
   Net weight: 35 1/4 ounces.
</P>
<P>
   Ingredients: Whole, peeled San Marzano plum tomatoes in natural
juices.
</P>
<P>
   Color, texture: Deep red; melts in your mouth.
</P>
<P>
   Taste: Excellent balance; subtle.
</P>
<P>
   Price: $2.39 at E. 48th Street Market (Dunwoody, Ga.).
</P>
<P>
   Cost per ounce: 6.78 cents.
</P>
<P>
   _ Bob Longino writes for the Atlanta Journal-Constitution.
</P>
