<HEADLINE>
IN THE SOUP ON A WINTER'S DAY
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By BEVERLY BUNDY 
c.1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   We have two requests for restaurant soups this week.
</P>
<P>
   Velma James of Fort Worth would like the recipe for the tortilla
soup served at The Worthington hotel. Saucier Jerome McKnight was
kind enough to send the recipe.
</P>
<P>
   The second recipe, from Brennan's in New Orleans, was requested
by Mollie Mims of Cleburn, Texas. (She also requested the recipe
for the restaurant's ``suicide cake,'' but Brennan's keeps that one
secret.)
</P>
<P>
   WORTHINGTON'S CHICKEN TORTILLA SOUP
</P>
<P>
   Serves 16
</P>
<P>
   2 tablespoons clarified butter
</P>
<P>
   1/4 cup minced garlic
</P>
<P>
   2 white onions, diced
</P>
<P>
   2 bell peppers, diced
</P>
<P>
   1 cup diced tomatoes (canned, drained tomatoes work fine)
</P>
<P>
   3 teaspoons tomato paste
</P>
<P>
   4 teaspoons ground cumin
</P>
<P>
   1 teaspoon chili powder
</P>
<P>
   1 teaspoon ground coriander
</P>
<P>
   1 teaspoon thyme
</P>
<P>
   1/2 jalapeno pepper, diced
</P>
<P>
   1/4 cup chicken base
</P>
<P>
   1 quart chicken or pork stock
</P>
<P>
   Cayenne pepper, to taste
</P>
<P>
   1 cup green chiles (drained canned chiles)
</P>
<P>
   2 cups diced chicken
</P>
<P>
   Monterey Jack cheese, chopped scallion and deep-fried corn
tortilla strips, for garnish.
</P>
<P>
   Saute garlic, onions and bell peppers in the butter until
softened. Add tomatoes and tomato paste and then add cumin, chili
powder, thyme, ground coriander and jalapenos. Combine chicken base
with the stock and add to garlic/tomato mixture; bring to boil,
reduce to simmer and let cook from 15 minutes to a half-hour. Stir
in drained green chiles and chicken. Taste and check for
seasonings; if not spicy enough, add cayenne pepper.
</P>
<P>
   Serve garnished with cheese, scallion and tortilla chips.
</P>
<P>
   Nutritional analysis per serving: 80 calories, 4 grams fat, 4
grams carbohydrates, 8 grams protein, 23 milligrams cholesterol,
115 milligrams sodium, 42 percent of calories from fat.
</P>
<P>
   _
</P>
<P>
   BRENNAN'S CREOLE ONION SOUP
</P>
<P>
   Serves 8
</P>
<P>
   1/2 cup butter
</P>
<P>
   1 large onion, thinly sliced
</P>
<P>
   1/2 cup all-purpose flour
</P>
<P>
   2 quarts beef stock
</P>
<P>
   2 tablespoons Worcestershire sauce
</P>
<P>
   1 teaspoon white pepper
</P>
<P>
   Salt to taste
</P>
<P>
   2 teaspoons yellow food coloring, optional
</P>
<P>
   1/4 cup freshly grated Parmesan cheese
</P>
<P>
   Melt butter in large pot and saute onion until tender, about 5
minutes. Blend in flour and cook mixture over medium heat another 5
minutes, stirring frequently. Add beef stock, Worcestershire sauce
and pepper. Adjust seasoning with salt to taste. If desired, add
the food coloring. Reduce heat and simmer until thickened, about 15
minutes. Sprinkle with Parmesan and serve.
</P>
<P>
   Nutritional analysis per serving: 183 calories, 14 grams fat, 11
grams carbohydrates, 5 grams protein, 34 milligrams cholesterol,
247 milligrams sodium, 68 percent of calories from fat.
</P>
<P>
   Requests:
</P>
<P>
   A reader writes with a problem I can't solve. Maybe someone else
can. The reader has a recipe for cherry mash deluxe, a candy that
was made with powdered sugar, maraschino cherries, sweetened
condensed milk and 2 boxes of creamy cherry frosting mix. Because
frosting is now sold ready-to-use, she doesn't know how to convert
the recipe. After calls to Duncan Hines, Pillsbury, Betty Crocker
and Borden, I came up with no solution. Perhaps a home cook has
solved this problem?
</P>
<P>
   Elva Garza of Fort Worth would like a recipe for salad dressing
using honey, vegetable oil, white wine vinegar and blue cheese. She
had this dressing on a salad of romaine lettuce, mandarin oranges,
purple onions and toasted almonds.
</P>
<P>
   (Beverly Bundy is food editor for the Fort Worth Star-Telegram.
Send recipes and requests to Beverly Bundy, Fort Worth
Star-Telegram, Box 1870, Fort Worth, Texas 76101. Or E-mail to
bbundy(at)star-telegram.com. Include a daytime phone number.
Responses to requests will be made only through this column. Visit
the Star-Telegram's online services on the World Wide Web:
www.star-telegram.com)
</P>
