<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-02-03 16:56 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A0428 &Cx1f; tie-z
u a &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-CIR-JOYSTICKS-COMPARE     02-03 0368
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-CIR-JOYSTICKS-COMPARE-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
JOYSTICKS COMPARISON LIST 
</HEADLINE>
   (af)  
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   Wingman Force
</P>
<P>
   Company: Logitech
</P>
<P>
   Platform: PC
</P>
<P>
   Price: $129.95
</P>
<P>
   Pro: Smooth cable-driven system; dual connector for either
serial or USB port.
</P>
<P>
   Cons: Large and heavy, takes up desk space
</P>
<P>
   Wingman Formula Force
</P>
<P>
   Company: Logitech
</P>
<P>
   Platform: PC
</P>
<P>
   Price: $179.95
</P>
<P>
   Pros: Durable, sleek design; best feel of all the wheels; dual
connector for either serial or USB port.
</P>
<P>
   Cons: Too little resistance in pedals.
</P>
