<HEADLINE>
IT WAS A MONSTER OF A GOOD MOVIE THEME
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By ROGERS CADENHEAD 
c.1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Q: I am a big fan of Godzilla. Can you please tell me the names
of all the Godzilla movies? _ J.J., Keller, Texas
</P>
<P>
   A: Godzilla was introduced in the 1954 Japanese film ``Gojira,''
which was re-edited and released in the United States as
``Godzilla, King of the Monsters.''
</P>
<P>
   Sony's ``Godzilla'' blockbuster from 1998 is one of the few
Godzilla films that weren't given several different English titles.
Here is a rundown of the rest of the Japanese Godzilla movies and
their U.S. release dates:
</P>
<P>
   ``Godzilla Raids Again'' (1955), ``King Kong vs. Godzilla''
(1963), ``Godzilla vs. Mothra'' (1964), ``Ghidorah the Three-Headed
Monster'' (1965), ``Godzilla vs. Sea Monster'' (1968), ``Son of
Godzilla'' (1969), ``Destroy All Monsters'' (1969), ``Godzilla vs.
Monster Zero'' (1970), ``Godzilla vs. the Smog Monster'' (1972),
``Godzilla's Revenge'' (1972), ``Revenge of Mechagodzilla'' (1975),
``Godzilla vs. Megalon'' (1976), ``Godzilla on Monster Island''
(1978), ``Godzilla vs. the Cosmic Monster'' (1978), ``Godzilla
1985'' (1985), ``Godzilla vs. Biollante'' (1993), ``Godzilla vs.
King Ghidora'' (1991), ``Godzilla vs. Mothra'' (1992), ``Godzilla
vs. Mechagodzilla'' (1993), ``Godzilla vs. Space Godzilla'' (1994)
and ``Godzilla vs. Destroyer'' (1995).
</P>
<P>
   In April, filming is reportedly going to begin on ``Godzilla
Millennium.''
</P>
<P>
   Q: What did the Liberty Bond flag look like when the United
States decided to join France and Great Britain in World War I?
Childe Hassam featured it in his painting ``Allies Day'' in 1917. _
V.C., Colleyville, Texas
</P>
<P>
   A: The design changed with each version of the loan program,
according to flag enthusiast Ralph Kelly.
</P>
<P>
   One version is depicted on Page 21 of ``The Flag Paintings of
Childe Hassam,'' a 1988 book by Ilene Susan Fort of the Los Angeles
County Museum of Art.
</P>
<P>
   That flag is white with a wide blue border and a single red
five-pointed star in the center. Fort's book is out of print.
</P>
<P>
   ``Other Hassam paintings ... seem to feature a broad red
rectangle surrounding a white field with up to 20 blue stars,''
Kelly said.
</P>
<P>
   Kelly belongs to the Flags of the World mailing list, one of the
best sources for flag information on the Internet. For more
information, visit the World Wide Web site www.flags.av.org.
</P>
<P>
   (Visit the Star-Telegram's online services on the World Wide
Web: www.star-telegram.com) &QL;
</P>
<P>
   .MDBU/
</P>
</TEXT>
