<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-02-03 18:47 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A0635 &Cx1f; ttx-z
r e &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-FILM-SIMPLYIRRESISTIB     02-03 0479
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-FILM-SIMPLYIRRESISTIBLE-TEX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
QUICK! DRIVE A STAKE THROUGH ITS HEART!
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By TODD CAMP 
c.1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   With all the hand-wringing that studios go through to pick out
movie titles, you'd think they'd try to make them critic-proof as
well. It's like parents who attempt to give their children
pre-adolescent jibe-proof names.
</P>
<P>
   If the people at 20th Century Fox had such foresight, they might
have avoided phrases like `` `Simply Irresistible' is actually
easily resistible'' or clever retitlings such as ``Simply
Irritating.''
</P>
<P>
   Sarah Michelle Gellar, riding her fame from skewering
bloodsuckers on the WB's ``Buffy the Vampire Slayer,'' has made
some less-than-stellar big-screen choices. After forgettable scream
queen portrayals in ``I Know What You Did Last Summer'' and
``Scream 2,'' Gellar shuns serial killers for a heaping helping of
gooey romance _ not that she's abandoned all things dark and creepy
just yet.
</P>
<P>
   Gellar is Amanda Shelton, the hapless chef of a struggling
Tribeca restaurant _ successful when her mother was at the stove.
Amanda lacks Mom's panache, so the customers have dwindled to a
hard-core few.
</P>
<P>
   Her fortunes change when she encounters what is presumably her
guardian angel or fairy godfather or whatever (the script never
makes it clear), who sells her a basket of magic beans, uh, I mean
crabs, and introduces her to the man she'll fall in love with, Sean
Patrick Flanery, who tries way to hard to make something of this
nothing part.
</P>
<P>
   With the help of a watchful guardian crab, Amanda becomes a
master chef overnight, whipping up dishes that give patrons a
plateful of her deepest emotions. She even wows Flanery's Tom
Bartlett, a hotshot young exec opening a chichi restaurant in an
uptown department store _ can you guess where this is going from
three miles away?
</P>
<P>
   Matters heat up quickly as magical occurrences become
commonplace: vanilla peach desserts cause the lovers to float over
pools of bubbling dry ice, caramel pastries spark the same kind of
aphrodisiac response as Herbal Essence shampoo. There's conflict,
there's resolution and everyone lives happily blah, blah, blah, but
you've figured it out five minutes into the movie. The whole thing
has about as much depth as an ``ABC Afterschool Special,'' but
that's really not fair to after-school specials.
</P>
<P>
   Gellar and Flanery make convincing young lovers, but the premise
of their relationship is such hurl-inducing hocus pocus, you're
begging for Puritans to show up with torches and giant stakes.
</P>
<P>
   And speaking of stakes, how 'bout putting aside the schmaltz and
making a ``Buffy'' movie, Sarah?
</P>
<P>
   ``Simply Irresistible'' is rated PG-13 for mild profanity, adult
subject matter and sexual innuendo.
</P>
<P>
   (Visit the Star-Telegram's online services on the World Wide
Web: www.star-telegram.com) &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-02-03-99 1847EST &QL; 
</TRAILER>
