   FED (Washington) _ Trapped between conflicting pressures at home
and abroad, the Federal Reserve voted Wednesday to leave interest
rates unchanged, keeping its hands off an economy that is either
gratifyingly robust or too strong for its own good. By Richard W.
Stevenson.
</P>
