<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-GAY-MARINE-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
GAY MARINE FEATURED IN THE NEW YORK TIMES ACTED IN PORNO FILMS 
</HEADLINE>
  (sw) 
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   The Advocate, a biweekly magazine about gay issues, reports that
a gay Marine who was the subject of a profile in The New York Times
Magazine last year appeared in several gay pornographic films while
he was on active duty.
</P>
<P>
   The profile, ``The Shadow Life of a Gay Marine,'' published on
June 28, 1998, in The New York Times Magazine, explored the
difficulties of living a clandestine homosexual life within the
``don't ask, don't tell'' structure of the U.S. military. The
Marine in the article, who insisted on remaining anonymous, was
identified in The Times by his first initial, ``R.'' He did not
inform The Times about the films.
</P>
<P>
   The disclosure of his film activities came when Capt. Rich
Merritt revealed that he is the Marine in an interview in the Jan.
19 issue of The Advocate. A reader who recognized Merritt from
several films contacted The Advocate, said Judy Wieder, its editor
in chief.
</P>
<P>
   About the disclosure, Adam Moss, editor of The Times Magazine,
said: ``Would we have liked to have known? Of course. But this is a
story about the complications of living under `don't ask, don't
tell,' and this revelation doesn't alter the story's truths.''
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
