-- A poster and a weight scale await removal at the armed forces
recruiting office on Times Square on Wednesday. The homely, rather
diner-esque building had held its asphalt perch in the middle of
Broadway and 43rd Street since 1946 is being replaced by a new,
$1.1 million, 500-square-foot station, designed to fit in with
Times Square's neo-BladeRunner milieu. (Chester Higgins Jr./New
York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT30) NEW YORK -- Feb. 3, 1999 -- TEXAS-FILM-DOCUMENTARY, 2-03
-- Filmmaker S.R. Bindler during a recent interview. His funny and
sometimes harrowing 97-minute documentary about a contest where
people try to win a truck by seeing how long they can keep one of
their hands on it has been quietly building a following and
received glowing reviews around the country over the last year.
(Frances Roberts/New York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT29) NEW YORK -- Feb. 3, 1999 -- NY-GUEST-ROOM-2, 2-03 -- The
bedroom in the home of Naomi Dunne, designed by architect Robert
Kahn. Ms. Donne sank $200,000 into this one-bedroom which was once
a wreck but whose ceilings reached nearly 14 feet. That left just
enough space to create room for guests. (Fred R. Conrad/New York
Times Photo)
</P>
