<P>
   (NYT24) OLYMPIA, Wash. -- Feb. 2, 1999 -- WOMEN-LEGISLATORS,
2-02 -- Female members of the Washington State Legislature during a
group photo last month. Washington State has highest percentage of
women in any state legislature in the nation's history. The women
of Olympia are among the more potent symbols of an electoral tide
that has brought record numbers of women into public office this
year, notably in the increasingly important state legislatures.
(Larry Davis/New York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT23) NEW YORK -- Feb. 3, 1999 -- DOCTORS-UNIONS, 2-03 --
Three of the doctors who support the idea of unionizing are, from
left, Robert Lee, Guy Isidore and James Leach. With doctors growing
angrier over managed care, the drive to unionize physicians has
sharply accelerated in recent months as thousands of them have
joined unions that are scrambling harder than ever to recruit them.
(Don Hogan Charles/New York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT22) HOLLYWOOD, Fla. -- Feb. 3, 1999 -- CIR-PHONE-CARD, 2-03
-- Todd Silverman uses a prepaid phone card to control spending.
When he runs low on time, he stops into a convenience store to
replenish his account. Prepaid phone services nearly doubled, to
1.8 million, in 1998 from their 1997 level of 533,000, according to
the Yankee Group, Boston-based telecommunications analysts. Prepaid
services are currently the fastest growing segment of the wireless
phone market. (John Ricksen/New York Times Photo)
</P>
