<P>
   (NYT19) PING YU, China -- Feb. 3, 1999 -- CHINA-ONE-CHILD-COX,
2-3 -- In the village of Ping Yu, old traditions like a Sunday
farmers' folk dance are mixing with new traditions that are not so
festive -- like sex-selection abortions. A couple giving birth to a
son is allowed one child. But a rural family that has a girl first
is permitted a second baby. Less than a half hour bus ride away
from Ping Yu, doctor are reputed to be willing and able to use an
ultrasound machine to help villagers learn the sex of a fetus.
(Marcia Kunstel/Cox News Service Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT18) WASHINGTON -- Feb. 3, 1999 -- IMPEACH-5, 2-03 -- Senate
Majority Leader Trent Lott jokes with reporters Wednesday on
Capitol Hill. With the impeachment trial set to reconvene Thursday,
House prosecutors questioned the last of three witnesses behind
closed doors and began a final drive to bring Lewinsky and two
Clinton advisers to testify in person before the Senate. (Stephen
Crowley/New York Times Photo)
</P>
