 UNDATED: to Denver).  
<TEXT>
<P>
   WESTERN CONFERENCE
</P>
<P>
   MIDWEST DIVISION:
</P>
<P>
   UTAH JAZZ
</P>
<P>
   Karl Malone and John Stockton often seem closer to retirement
than a championship, but they manage to somehow get the Jazz
peaking by the playoffs. Stockton, who turns 37 in March, will
continue to split minutes with Howard Eisley. Bryon Russell needs
to have a monster start, especially while Greg Foster rehabilitates
a broken ankle. Utah went on an archeological dig for their one
off-season acquisition, digging up former Jazz forward Thurl
Bailey. Jeff Hornacek, like Malone, is 35. They're old, cranky and,
yes, still the best passing team in basketball. Dead quiet after
Michael Jordan stole its soul the last two seasons, the Delta
Center will finally host a championship party for the home team in
late June.
</P>
<P>
   Additions: Thurl Bailey (free agent).
</P>
<P>
   Key Losses: C Antoine Carr (free agent, Houston), F Chris Morris
(free agent).
</P>
<P>
   HOUSTON ROCKETS
</P>
<P>
   They lost one Hall of Famer (Clyde Drexler to retirement) only
to bring in another (Scottie Pippen). The Rockets have not rebuilt
as much as they have reloaded. But so much depends on whether
Pippen, Hakeem Olajuwon and Charles Barkley can get through the
season injury-free. Losing Mario Elie to free agency was key. Like
the Knicks' Charlie Ward, Matt Maloney is more of a serviceable
point guard than a floor general. But with three of the Top 50
players of all time to complement him, he may be enough to get
Houston back to the finals.
</P>
<P>
   Additions: F Scottie Pippen (trade with Bulls), G Michael
Dickerson (draft, No. 14, Arizona), G Bryce Drew (draft, No. 14,
Valparaiso), C Antoine Carr (free agent, Jazz), F Anthony Miller
(free agent, Hawks).
</P>
<P>
   Key Losses: G Clyde Drexler (retired), G Mario Elie (free agent,
San Antonio), C Kevin Willis (traded to Toronto).
</P>
<P>
   SAN ANTONIO SPURS
</P>
<P>
   On the surface, they upgraded their roster with Steve Kerr,
Mario Elie and second-year point guard Antonio Daniels, acquired in
a trade with Vancouver. But Tim Duncan and David Robinson still
don't have that offensive-minded backcourt player to alleviate
scoring pressure. They're deeper than a year ago, and Elie brings
the kind of attitude and edge the Spurs need in the playoffs. But
getting past the Lakers and Utah is too much to ask this season.
</P>
<P>
   Additions: G Steve Kerr (trade with Bulls), G Mario Elie (free
agent, Rockets), G Antonio Daniels (trade with Grizzlies), F Jerome
Kersey (free agent, SuperSonics).
</P>
<P>
   Key Losses: F Chuck Person (traded to Chicago), F Carl Herrera
(traded to Vancouver), G Vinny Del Negro (free agent, Milwaukee), G
Jaren Jackson (free agent).
</P>
<P>
   MINNESOTA TIMBERWOLVES
</P>
<P>
   Still phenoms after two and three seasons, respectively, Stephon
Marbury and Kevin Garnett are must-see TV. And bringing back the
underrated center Dean Garrett from Denver and getting point guard
Bobby Jackson was a nice off-season move. But the losses hurt. If
it wasn't Tom Gugliotta spurning the franchise for less money in
Phoenix, losing clubhouse sages like Terry Porter and Sam Mitchell
_ veterans who talked to and nurtured the young stars _ was also a
blow. If the kiddie corps T'Wolves have one thing going for them,
it's that they won't get tired playing 50 games in 90 days. The big
question for Minnesota is whether they can re-sign Marbury by
season's end.
</P>
<P>
   Additions: F Joe Smith (free agent, 76ers), G Bobby Jackson, C
Dean Garrett (trade with Nuggets), G Malik Sealy (free agent,
Pistons), C Radoslav Nesterovic (draft, No. 17, Italy).
</P>
<P>
   Key Losses: F Tom Gugliotta (free agent, Phoenix), G Micheal
Williams (traded to Toronto), C Cherokee Parks (free agent,
Vancouver), G Terry Porter (free agent, Miami), G Sam Mitchell
(free agent).
</P>
<P>
   DENVER NUGGETS
</P>
<P>
   In one of the great off-season makeovers of the past decade, GM
Dan Issel put a team with more structural problems than Mir back in
playoff contention. Nick Van Exel and the return of Antonio McDyess
make for one of the most lethal offensive combinations in the West.
The Kansas rookie Raef LaFrentz will help immediately along with
the back-up point guard Chauncey Billups. Overcoming the culture of
losing should not be that difficult. As for making the playoffs,
that's a long shot.
</P>
<P>
   Additions: F Antonio McDyess (free agent, Suns), G Nick Van Exel
(trade with Lakers), G Chauncey Billups (trade with Raptors), F
Raef LaFrentz (draft, No. 3, Kansas), G Monty Williams (free agent,
Spurs), C Keon Clark (draft, No. 13, UNLV), F Johnny Taylor (trade
with Magic).
</P>
<P>
   Key Losses: F Johnny Newman (free agent, Cleveland), F LaPhonso
Ellis (free agent), F Harold Ellis (free agent, New Jersey), C Dean
Garrett, G Bobby Jackson (traded to Minnesota), F Tony Battie
(traded to Los Angeles Lakers).
</P>
<P>
   DALLAS MAVERICKS
</P>
<P>
   With all Don Nelson's tinkering, the GM's best move may have
been flying to Germany with the owner Ross Perot Jr. and getting a
first-hand look at Dirk Nowitzki, the 6-foot-9 forward who shoots
the 3-point bomb with aplomb. Nowitzki has already impressed in two
preseason games, and will make an immediate impact on a club in
need of help. Steve Nash was another good acquisition. The
Mavericks have more talent, but chemistry will take a while.
</P>
<P>
   Additions: G Steve Nash (trade with Suns), C Hot Rod Williams
(free agent, Suns), F Gary Trent (free agent, Raptors), F Dirk
Nowitzki (draft, No. 9, Germany).
</P>
<P>
   Key Losses: C Eric Riley (free agent, Celtics), F Kurt Thomas
(free agent, Knicks), F Bubba Wells (traded to Phoenix), F Martin
Muursepp (traded to Phoenix).
</P>
<P>
   VANCOUVER GRIZZLIES
</P>
<P>
   Locking up Shareef Abdur-Rahim through 2005 helped the
Grizzlies, but putting the right pieces around him may take time.
Bryant Reeves is improving and the rookie Mike Bibby will try to do
what Antonio Daniels could not: run the point guard position
effectively. Still, the Grizzlies remain on the periphery of the
middle-echelon teams.
</P>
<P>
   Additions: G Mike Bibby (draft, No. 2, Arizona), F Carl Herrera
(trade with Spurs), C Cherokee Parks (free agent, Timberwolves), G
Felipe Lopez (draft, No. 24, St. John's).
</P>
<P>
   Key Losses: G Antonio Daniels (traded to San Antonio), F George
Lynch (free agent).
</P>
