<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-OLY-DRUGS-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
IOC ROLE ON DOPING IS QUESTIONED
</HEADLINE>
  (bl)  
By PAUL L. MONTGOMERY   
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service    
<TEXT>
<P>
   LAUSANNE, Switzerland _ Participants at the international
conference on sports doping expressed broad support Wednesday for
creation of a worldwide enforcement agency, but there was
considerable disagreement on its composition and powers as the
International Olympic Committee continued to face attacks on its
credibility.
</P>
<P>
   Richard Pound, a Canadian lawyer and IOC vice president who is
drafting a proposal on the agency to be considered by the
conference on Thursday, acknowledged that the IOC has had to scale
back its plans to be at the center of the agency. Pound said
national governments would have a much larger role than
anticipated, a reflection of the widespread skepticism about the
IOC's leadership ability in the wake of the burgeoning bribery
scandals involving host cities.
</P>
<P>
   The contentiousness went beyond just the makeup of the agency.
There was further division over the severity of punishment for
athletes caught cheating, pitting the IOC against some of the
federations that govern individual sports internationally. And the
IOC executive board was challenged on its decision to change the
voting procedure for selecting host cities.
</P>
<P>
   Pound said that even if the new drug agency was approved in
principle Thursday, it would be several months before its
composition could be planned.
</P>
<P>
   ``We have a wonderful opportunity to marry the public side and
the sports side in this agency,'' he said. ``But it will take time
for the governments to work out the details.''
</P>
<P>
   Tuesday, government representatives from the United States and
most of the countries of Western Europe called for reform of the
IOC so that it can regain credibility to take part in the
antidoping effort. Pound said it was possible the new agency, if
approved, would have as much as 50 percent representation from
public authorities, whereas before the conference the IOC had
anticipated no more than 20 percent. It was an indication of the
increasing inclination of governments to take antidoping
enforcement out of the hands of sports bodies, as happened last
summer in the Tour de France.
</P>
<P>
   Speaking on behalf of the 15-member European Union, British
Sports Minister Tony Banks rejected the proposal giving the IOC a
leading role in the agency.
</P>
<P>
   Other items also remained to be resolved on the conference's
final day. The IOC and many athletes' groups want a minimum
two-year ban from competition for those testing positive for
performance-enhancing drugs. The international soccer, cycling and
tennis federations, however, have said the ban is too long and have
refused to follow IOC policy. Keba Mbaye of Senegal, a former World
Court judge who heads the IOC group studying juridical aspects of
doping, indicated Wednesday that exceptions would have to be made
to the two-year rule.
</P>
<P>
   Sebastian Coe of Britain, two-time Olympic 1,500 meter champion
and now a Conservative party politician, said authorities should
not accept anything less than a two-year ban.
</P>
<P>
   In another development, a number of IOC members attending the
conference expressed displeasure with new regulations promulgated
by the IOC last week to take away their voting rights for sites of
future Games. Voting by the full membership on sites has been
regarded as the prime cause of the corruption scandal, and the IOC
wants to restrict selection to a 15-member group.
</P>
<P>
   Some members expressed resentment that the whole voting
membership was punished for the actions of a few. The proposal is
scheduled to come up for a vote at an emergency IOC session March
17-18. A two-thirds vote of the 106 members is needed for adoption.
</P>
<P>
   It is rare for the full membership to go against leadership
positions. But Italian IOC member Mario Pescante was quoted as
saying: ``It's impossible the General Assembly will approve this
proposal. ``I'm sure the executive board will have to find a new
solution before then.''  &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-02-03-99 2213EST &QL; 
</TRAILER>
