<SLUG> BC-BKN-LAKERS-NOTES-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
RODMAN INTRIGUES LAKERS
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By HOWARD BECK  
 c.1999 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   INGLEWOOD _ Dennis Rodman hasn't even stepped onto the premises
yet, and already he's Topic No. 1 within the walls of the Great
Western Forum.
</P>
<P>
   As the Lakers wrestle internally over whether the seven-time
rebounding champion is worth the trouble, they remain outwardly
noncommittal about the prospect of obtaining his services.
</P>
<P>
   Lakers executive Jerry West admits the club is, at the least,
intrigued by the talented, tattoed, unpredictable, enigmatic,
colorful, controversial, cross-dressing power forward with four
championship rings.
</P>
<P>
   But West won't say how intrigued.
</P>
<P>
   ``To really say there's any substance to it . . . it's bandied
about in the office. But we have no idea if there will even be any
interest on his part to start with,'' West said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
   Which begs the question, if Rodman is indeed interested in the
Lakers, how interested are they in him?
</P>
<P>
   ``I really don't know that,'' West said. ``People have to want
you sometimes before you decide those things.
</P>
<P>
   ``I think we're all aware he does bring a basketball ingredient
that's been proven. His teams seem to win. He's one of the smartest
players to play this game, period. He knows how to do it. Plus he's
got great energy and enthusiasm.''
</P>
<P>
   So the Lakers are making inquiries. Rodman and owner Jerry Buss
have chatted and West has talked to Rodman's new agent, Steve
Chasman of talent agency ICM. Chasman, however, wasn't a registered
player agent as of Wednesday, according to the players association,
though he was expected to file for certification.
</P>
<P>
   As the story took on a life of its own, as everything involving
Rodman does, West said just enough to keep the plot afloat, even
while downplaying the possible conclusion.
</P>
<P>
   ``These questions are all really meaningless,'' he told
reporters. ``There's so much more to this than just maybe us having
a desire to talk to him. And we have not talked to him personally.
. . .
</P>
<P>
   ``Sitting here trying to speculate on something that we really
have had no definitive discussions on is just filling up space in a
newspaper and creating a lot mote publicity and lot more
controversy. Which I'm sure Dennis likes.''
</P>
<P>
   Rodman made $4.5 million last year. The Lakers can only offer
the $1 million veteran's minimum, but Rodman doesn't appear to have
any better offers, and other teams he likes have ruled out hiring
him, including the Houston Rockets on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
   But Buss, a partier and playboy in his own right, has an
affinity for Rodman.
</P>
<P>
   ``I talked to Jerry about it,'' West said, ``and he's always
liked Dennis personally and he knows him personally and I'll leave
it at that.''
</P>
<P>
   Shaquille O'Neal, a longtime Rodman critic but now his greatest
advocate, began lobbying openly for his services this week. It will
be O'Neal who benefits the most from Rodman's rebounding and
defense.
</P>
<P>
   Of West's efforts, O'Neal said: ``I'm happy. Hopefully something
can get resolved.''
</P>
<P>
   Some Lakers quietly express reservations about Rodman's
presence, but overall he's got support in the locker room, where
his talents weigh more heavily than his antics.
</P>
<P>
   ``I'm sure he'll test us, I'm sure he'll be Dennis,'' Rick Fox
said. ``We're not expecting him to be anything else. That means
whatever comes along with that, those 13-14 (rebounds) are pretty
nice to have too.''
</P>
<P>
   Said Derek Harper, ``As long as he doesn't dress in drag and sit
next to me, he's cool.''
</P>
<P>
   Ouch report: Fox sat out practice for the second straight day
because of soreness in both ankles and knees. He said the problem
was a new pair of shoe insoles that gave insufficient shock
absorption, but he expects to be ready for Friday night's season
opener.
</P>
<P>
   Robert Horry was diagnosed with an upper respiratory infection
Wednesday and is listed as day-to-day.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
